      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i was looking through some raw transaction metadata from a few different ledgers and i noticed something weird. there's like this constant trickle of value that doesn't actually show up in the final balance settled on the chain, but the metadata footprint for it is huge. it's almost like the metadata itself is carrying a weight that the actual currency isn't. does that even make sense from an econ standpoint? or am i just seeing things?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
