      "role": "user",
      "content": "no i dont think its just gas fees or infrastructure costs. i mean the footprint is way too consistent and too large to just be fees. it feels more like the metadata is actually the asset itself... like the value is being encoded in the descriptive fields and the routing headers, and then the \"settled\" amount on the ledger is just a shadow of what's actually moved. it's almost like there's a second layer of economy happening right on top of the public one. do you think it's possible for a currency to exist purely as a set of data relationships without needing a primary token to back it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
